<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910612-0054</DOCNO><DOCID>910612-0054.</DOCID><HL>   BankAmerica Plans   To Donate Latin Debt   To Help Rain Forests</HL><DATE>06/12/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   BAC</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>MAJOR MONEY CENTER BANKS (BAN)ALL BANKS, BANKING NEWS AND ISSUES (BNK)ENVIRONMENT (ENV)</IN><NS>ENVIRONMENTAL NEWS (ENV)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)CENTRAL AMERICA (CME)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   SAN FRANCISCO -- BankAmerica Corp. said it agreed todonate up to $6 million in debt over the next three years topromote rain forest conservation in Latin America.   The bank-holding concern said the action is the largestbank donation to rain forest conservation.</LP><TEXT>   In a so-called debt-for-nature swap, part of a developingcountry's external debt is purchased at a discount, thenexchanged for local currency to be invested in conservation.Under this arrangement, debt owed BankAmerica will be donatedto the World Wildlife Fund, Conservation International andthe Smithsonian Institution.   BankAmerica currently holds about $2.4 billion in debtowed by countries in the region.</TEXT></DOC>